description:
## Problem
Proactive compact fires at flat usage.percent >= 0.9. This ignores model output-token reservation and breaks on smaller windows.

Reference (Role Model): effectiveWindow = contextWindow - min(maxOutputTokens, 20000); threshold = effective - 13k. The 13k buffer is specifically sized so one large tool result + the compaction call fit.

pi-harness 90% = 20k headroom on 200k window (fine), but only 12.8k on a 128k window (tight — one big file read overshoots). Does not subtract model max-output reservation.

## Fix
Fire based on absolute token headroom, not just percent. In proactive-compact.ts:

```ts
const PROACTIVE_COMPACT_HEADROOM_TOKENS = 15_000;

export function shouldTriggerProactiveCompact(
  usage: ContextUsage | undefined,
): boolean {
  if (!usage || usage.tokens === null || usage.percent === null) return false;
  // Fire when fewer than ~15k tokens of headroom remain, regardless of percent
  return usage.contextWindow - usage.tokens < PROACTIVE_COMPACT_HEADROOM_TOKENS;
}
```

ContextUsage already exposes tokens + contextWindow (confirmed in types.d.ts:192).

## Note
This is a redundant EARLY trigger — pi-coding-agent core has its own threshold. The question is whether to fire earlier to give more headroom. 15k token-buffer is more robust across model sizes than 90%.

## Files
- EDIT: `proactive-compact.ts` (shouldTriggerProactiveCompact)

## Acceptance
- Fires consistently across 128k / 200k / 1M context windows
- Depends on: pi-harness-runtime-r53 (tests cover new logic)

## Problem
No failure-based circuit breaker — only a flat 10-min time cooldown.

Reference implementation (Role Model): MAX_CONSECUTIVE_AUTOCOMPACT_FAILURES = 3. After 3 fails, stops trying and surfaces to user (prevents pathological API-call loops; telemetry showed sessions with 50+ consecutive failures wasting a huge volume of calls/day).

pi-harness: onError resets proactiveCompactInFlight but doesn't count failures. A flaky compaction retries every 10 min indefinitely while context climbs toward blocking limit.

## Fix
Add a failure counter in index.ts:

```ts
let consecutiveCompactFailures = 0;
const MAX_PROACTIVE_COMPACT_FAILURES = 3;

// in maybeTriggerProactiveCompact, before triggering:
if (consecutiveCompactFailures >= MAX_PROACTIVE_COMPACT_FAILURES) return;

// in onComplete: consecutiveCompactFailures = 0
// in onError: consecutiveCompactFailures += 1
```

## Files
- EDIT: `index.ts` (maybeTriggerProactiveCompact + onError/onComplete callbacks)

## Acceptance
- After 3 consecutive failures, proactive compact stops firing for the session
- Success resets the counter
- Console logs when circuit breaker trips
